Recommends: strace
Description: monitor and alert on runaway Koha Starman workers
 A small daemon that periodically scans /proc for Koha Starman worker
 processes and posts a Slack alert when a worker exceeds a memory
 threshold. On alert, it takes a forensic snapshot that always
 includes /proc/PID/{wchan,syscall,stack} and can optionally run
 `gdb -batch -p PID -ex bt` (on by default), `strace -p PID` for a
 configurable window (off by default), and signal a cooperating
 SIGUSR2 handler in plack.psgi for a Perl-level backtrace. The tail
 of the combined capture is included in the Slack message. Designed
 to be installed on Koha hosts and managed by systemd.
